description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;HMP Liverpool is a Category B male prison with an excellent HMIP/CQC Report (published 14th January 2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Better Health Liverpool (BHL) has transformed the healthcare service into a dynamic, forward thinking place of work were staff are supported and valued for their contribution. The nursing team have been recognised for their outstanding practice and collaborative partnerships and are rightly proud of the Nurse Led Model approach.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a vacancy for an outstanding Primary Care Clinical Lead to engage with this award-winning team in continuing its healthcare transformation. The successful candidate will provide clinical expertise to a diverse Primary care team and form part of the senior management group for Better Health Liverpool.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for somebody with excellent skills who can clinically prioritise and manage the patient journey within this secure environment. Experience of offender health is desirable however we would welcome and individual who is multiskilled across complex care pathways.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Offender health is a very exciting and challenging specialism with a significant Public Health and Long-Term Condition agenda – significantly, the management of long term conditions and acute presentations represent a large cohort of this patient group and requires individuals to have an understanding of trauma informed care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role requires excellent communication skills and dynamic work practices. We are looking for somebody who can deliver at least equivalent care to that of the community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for implementing policy and procedure and will need to be able to support the nursing team to ensure care of the highest standard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work to uphold Spectrum Community Health’s Values. &lt;span&gt;If you are interested in a further conversation, please call 0151 530 4030 (Stella Hannaway, Head of Transformation BHL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
